reviews.review_text: John Mayer said this on Sirius FM ... “It’s John Mayer here playing some of my favorite Grateful Dead tracks, and I want to get into one that was so moving and affecting that I actually remember where I was,” Mayer said on SiriusXM’s Grateful Dead Channel. “I was on the way to a girlfriend’s house on the corner of Outpost and Franklin. I’m now moving my hands to draw the streets. That’s how important and impactful this song was. I remember exactly where I was, and it is a one-of-a-kind rendition of ‘Scarlet Begonias’ into ‘Fire on the Mountain’ because it’s almost a reggae dub version.”
